{"questionId":"19782","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The water temperature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in Lake Windermere is measured on the first day of eight&nbsp;consecutive months <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>)</mo></math> from January to August (months <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>) and the results are shown&nbsp;below. The value for May (month <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>) has been accidently deleted.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5573a504d6449e0b54c97ef52754c0732073c284.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use your line to find an estimate for the water temperature on the first day of&nbsp;May.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2671</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[2 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19782","referenceCode":"EXN.1.SL.TZ0.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Use your line to find an estimate for the water temperature on the first day of May.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}